                            <comment id="12758012" author="alangates" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2009 21:16:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;You need to add a unit test that checks that this works when there is a + in the path.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, a more general question:  I&apos;m guessing that &apos;+&apos; isn&apos;t the only mishandled character.  Are there others that should be checked?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12758394" author="tlipcon" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2009 20:50:17 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;You need to add a unit test that checks that this works when there is a + in the path. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is very difficult to test - we&apos;d need to add several more ant rules to build a jar into the test directory with a + in it and get that on the classpath for tests. findContainingJar itself is not currently tested.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Also, a more general question: I&apos;m guessing that &apos;+&apos; isn&apos;t the only mishandled character. Are there others that should be checked?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s well-known that URLDecoder actually decodes x-www-form-urlencoded rather than true URL encoding. The spec for that encoding is here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/MarkUp/html-spec/html-spec_8.html#SEC8.2.1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.w3.org/MarkUp/html-spec/html-spec_8.html#SEC8.2.1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As far as I&apos;ve been able to find, &apos;+&apos; is the only difference, except for perhaps newlines which can&apos;t occur in pathnames afaik.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;More info here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Percent-encoding#The_application.2Fx-www-form-urlencoded_type&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Percent-encoding#The_application.2Fx-www-form-urlencoded_type&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12759188" author="alangates" created="Thu, 24 Sep 2009 18:29:04 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, if it&apos;s hard to test in an automated way that&apos;s fine.  To test it manually, is it sufficient to create a jar with a + in the path, register it in a Pig Latin script, and then use a UDF from that jar in the script?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12763271" author="tlipcon" created="Wed, 7 Oct 2009 22:16:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, I think that would be a good manual test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12765325" author="alangates" created="Wed, 14 Oct 2009 01:10:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch checked in.  Thanks Todd.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
